How Do Health, Ethics and Developer Kinship Correlate to Programmer Salary?¶

Guiding Questions¶

1. Do health conscious programmers make more money?¶

2. Will prioritizing ethical concerns in the workplace cost you?¶

3. Does competitiveness or comraderie correspond to higher earnings?¶

Survey Responses that will Help Answer our Questions¶

Income: ConvertedSalary

Health: SkipMeals, ErgonomicDevices, Exercise

Ethics: EthicsChoice, EthoicsReport, EthicalImplications

Kinship: AgreeDisagree1, AgreeDisagree2, AgreeDisagree3

Let's Clean our Data¶

What Factors Should We Control For?¶

To make sure we're controlling for as many variables unrelated to health, ethics and kinship as possible, we need to group our respondents into cohorts that remove as many other factors as possible.

Based on the response questions, it seems reasonable to group based on employment status, years employed (since the longer you've worked the more you are likely to make), and education degree (since this could impact earnings).
